Description.value:
This is a template for scenario-specific inbound processing flows that you can copy and adapt to your needs:
- Add and configure the sender adapter.
- In the "Set SAP headers" content modifier, maintain headers SAP_Sender and SAP_SenderInterface required to read the Partner Directory entries in the subsequent generic pipeline steps.
- If you like to define customer specific header properties to be able to search message logs based on payload data, first define exchange properties by parsing the incoming XML message, then maintain name/value pairs in the header customHeaderProperties following the pattern: prop1:${property.prop1}|prop2:${property.prop2}. If your incoming payload is not in XML format, you may need to create a script to parse the body of your message. Optionally, you can define the custom header properties in the scenario-specific inbound conversion flow (pipeline step 03) if applicable.
- In case of multiple Service Interface Operations, maintain mapping between Operation and Message Type adhering to following naming convention: For each operation create exchange property with name SAP-MT2OP-<Operation name> and value <Message Type name>.
- Maintain exception handling to your needs.
- Delete flow steps that you do not need.
For more details, please refer to the documentation (see link in Documents section of the package).
